  "articleSummary": "This tutorial provides a step-by-step guide for configuring UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall) on a Debian/Ubuntu Docker host server. The core argument is that a properly hardened firewall is essential for Docker security, achieved by setting default deny rules, explicitly allowing only necessary ports (SSH, HTTP, HTTPS, and Docker internal traffic), and testing with nmap. The intended audience is system administrators or developers managing Docker hosts, and the tone is instructional with cautionary warnings about not locking out SSH access.",
